parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Fuel Pump Inlet Bushing/Fuel Control Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel pump inlet bushing or fuel control housing can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when the engine is under pressure. This can result in serious injuries or accidents.
symptoms: fuel leaking onto the driver's leg or other body parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Final Drive Failure in BMW Motorcycles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause significant roughness in the rear wheel rotation, pronounced rumbling noise at high speeds, and potentially lead to loss of control or accidents.

vibration or shaking of the motorcycle.
